      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BANDIT ALEX (6) goes very well this trip starting eight times for three wins and two minors. Below best last time at Wentworth Park (29.79) in a NG, finishing a 2 length fourth. Has the ability and should feature. ZIPPING DOWNEY (2) comes off an average effort last start when seventh at Wentworth Park over 520m behind Duran Sting (30.65) in a Grade 5. The form out of his last race has been franked. Has ability and can atone. OVATION KEY (3) had been racing well with a Maiden win three back then placed next time before missing the frame latest at Wentworth Park. This looks easier and expected to improve sharply. ANCESTRAL QUEEN (1) missed the placings here most recently but can sneak into the finish with the right run.",
